Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Halve, peel and
finely chop the @onion{1}(finely chopped). Slice open the @97% pork sausages{500%g},
remove the meat and discard the skin. Break the sausage meat into 2cm chunks and
keep to one side. Mix the @water{400%ml} with the @chicken stock pot{1} in a
#measuring jug{}. Stir well to dissolve the stock pot, then pour in the
@tomato passata{2%cups} and mix together.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a large (ovenproof if you have one)
#saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} and a pinch of
@salt{}. Stir and toast until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer the crumbs from
your pan to a #plate{}, wipe out the pan with some #kitchen paper{}. Add the
sausage chunks to your pan with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}, turning frequently to brown them evenly. Add the onion, stir
and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the @risotto rice{350%g} to your pan and stir together to make sure the
rice is coated in oil. Pour in the tomato stock mixture. Stir together, bring
to the boil and cover with a #lid{}. 

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer the mixture to an ovenproof dish at this
> point and cover with a lid or tin foil.

Pop on the middle shelf of your oven and cook, ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @cucumber{1} lengthways. Slice half of it into thin half
moons and the other half into batons (in case anyone doesn't like salad). Squeeze
the @lemon{1}(juiced) juice into a #small bowl{} along with the @honey{1},
@olive oil{3%tbsp}, a pinch of salt and @ground black pepper{}. Whisk together
with a #fork{}. This is your dressing. Pop the cucumber slices and
@baby leaves{1%bag} in another #bowl{}. Roughly chop half the @basil{1}(chopped),
discard the stalks.

If the rice and sausage in your risotto isn't cooked yet then just pop it back
into your oven for ~{5%minutes} more.

> The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, add the chopped basil, @grated hard Italian style cheese{80%g}
(leave one pinch for the salad) and @unsalted butter{30%g} to the risotto and
stir together until melted. Taste and add salt and black pepper if you feel it
needs it. Add the whole basil leaves to the salad.

Serve the sausage risotto in #bowls{}. Sprinkle the crumbs on top of the adults'
risotto (and on top of the children's too if they want them!), dress anyone's
salad who wants it with the dressing and the pinch of remaining cheese and serve
the cucumber salad on the side. Pop the cucumber batons in a little bowl in the
middle of the table to share. Enjoy!